President Obama released a statement expressing his joy at the safe return of Sergeant Bowe Bergdahl, who had been held captive for almost five years. He also acknowledged the sacrifices made by Bergdahl's parents throughout the ordeal. The President emphasized America's commitment to leaving no soldier behind on the battlefield and mentioned the other troops who are still missing or unaccounted for. He thanked the Amir of Qatar for his assistance in securing Bergdahl's release and expressed gratitude for the support of the Government of Afghanistan. The President also mentioned the United States' commitment to supporting the Afghan people and their reconciliation process for a stable and unified Afghanistan.